article.headline: Wis-Green Bay 65, Ill-Chicago 55
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Ryan Evanochko scored 21 points and Ryan Tillema added 15 from behind the arc as Wisconsin-Green Bay beat Illinois-Chicago 65-55 Wednesday night. Evanochko hit 6-of-6 from the free throw line and Tillema was responsible for five of eight 3-pointers by the Phoenix (15-12, 7-7 Horizon League), who held the Flames scoreless for the final 4:39 of the game. Illinois-Chicago (10-17, 5-9) got 15 points from Josh Mayo and 10 from Robert Bush. Jovan Stefanov grabbed a game-high 10 rebounds and finished with seven points for the Flames. The Phoenix held Illinois-Chicago to 29 percent first-half shooting but had just a four-point advantage, 33-29, at the break. But Wisconsin-Green Bay pulled ahead in the second and finished at better than 40 percent shooting for the game compared with less than 30 percent overall shooting for the Flames.
